# meme-maker — sensible gitignore

# Dependencies
node_modules/
# (package-lock.json is intentionally committed for reproducible installs)

# Generated / temp
frames/
*.tmp
__*.mp4
__*.gif
*.log

# Output artifacts we usually don't want in git
meme.gif
meme.mp4
clip.mp4
clip.mp3
gifs/
videos/
audio/
*.mp4
*.mp3
*.gif
*.png

# But keep some example inputs
!*_terminal.html
!test_term.html
!seki-term.html

# OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# The old standalone meme (keep it if you want, but it's duplicated logic)
# Memes/mememaker.sh   ← uncomment if you want to ignore it
# AI coding assistant local memory (personal working files)
#
# project-memory.md = high-signal AI context file (primary file future Grok/Claude/Cursor/etc. should read)
# project-journal.md = optional human narrative / story file (the enjoyable "what happened" record)
#
# These are personal journals for whoever is actively using the tools here.
# They add noise to the repo and can trigger negative reactions from people
# who dislike visible AI tooling. Anyone using similar tools will have their own anyway.
#
# Only remove this ignore (or force-add the files) if your team *explicitly*
# wants to share the session history as part of the project.

project-memory.md
project-journal.md

# Legacy (previous single-file name) — safe to keep
project.grok

.grok/

# Grok scratch / execution workspace (machine-local, recommended to ignore)
# Used for temporary run scripts and logs when the AI cannot execute commands directly
.grok-scratch/
*.grok-tmp